extend ../../layouts/nested-2
block main
	h2.flex-title deleteCookie()
	p
		| The <code>deleteCookie()</code> method maps directly to
		| <a href="http://webdriver.io/api/cookie/deleteCookie.html">deleteCookie() method</a> on WebdriverIO. Let's see
		| how we would execute this command on a cookie called <code>docCookie</code> that is already set in the browser.
	pre.language-javascript.line-numbers
		code
			| 'use strict';
			| <br>
			| var drive = require('datadriver');
			| <br>
			| drive.execute({
			|   "execute": {
			|     "action": "redirect",
			|     "page": "api/execute/deleteCookie.html"
			|   }
			| });
			| <br>
			| drive.execute({
			|   "execute": {
			|     "action": "deleteCookie",
			|     "name": "docCookie"
			|   }
			| });
	p And this is our expected output:
	pre.language-bash.line-numbers
		code
			| $ grunt webdriver:execute --url=http://datadriver.io
			| Running "webdriver:execute" (webdriver) task
			| <br>
			| ⚙ redirecting to "http://datadriver.io/api/execute/deleteCookie.html"
			| ⚙ deleting a cookie with name: "docCookie"
			| <br>
			| 0 passing
	.flash-notice
		p If no cookie is found, the action will execute without errors, but in effect, nothing will happen.
block scripts
	script.
		if (document.cookie.replace(/(?:(?:^|.*;\s*)docCookie\s*\=\s*([^;]*).*$)|^.*$/, "$1") !== "true") {
			document.cookie = "docCookie=true; expires=Fri, 31 Dec 9999 23:59:59 GMT; path=/";
		}